---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service - telMAX"
  description="The terms and conditions that govern your use of telMAX services and website."
>
  <section class="section bg-green hero-block">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-block__inner">
        <span class="pill">Legal</span>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="prose">
        <p class="updated">Last updated: January 2026</p>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of telMAX services and
          this website. They are provided as a starting template - please have
          them reviewed by qualified legal counsel before publishing.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Services</h2>
        <p>
          telMAX provides residential and business internet, TV and home phone
          services where our network is available. Service availability, speeds
          and features depend on your location and chosen plan.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Accounts and eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          You must provide accurate account information and are responsible for
          activity on your account. Some services require a qualifying internet
          plan and a minimum service term.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Pricing and billing</h2>
        <p>
          Promotional pricing applies to eligible new customers for the stated
          term. Regular rates apply afterward. A network access fee may apply to
          new customers, and taxes are extra. Charges are billed monthly.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Equipment</h2>
        <p>
          Equipment such as the eero WiFi system may be provided on a rental
          basis and remains the property of telMAX. You agree to return it in
          good condition if service ends.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>
          You agree not to use telMAX services for unlawful activity, to disrupt
          the network, or in any way that interferes with other customers.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Home phone and 911</h2>
        <p>
          Home phone service is delivered over the internet. 911 emergency
          calling may be unavailable during a power outage or internet
          interruption. We recommend keeping an alternative means of contacting
          emergency services.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Cancellation</h2>
        <p>
          You may cancel service in accordance with your plan terms. Early
          cancellation during a committed term may be subject to applicable
          charges.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Changes to these Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use of our
          services after changes take effect constitutes acceptance.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these Terms? Email
          <a href="mailto:support@telmax.com" style="text-decoration:underline">support@telmax.com</a>
          or call 1-844-483-5629.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-block { padding-top: clamp(64px, 9vw, 120px); }
</style>
